\begin_layout Standard
The Hamiltonian for graphene near the Dirac point 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{K}$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{H}_{\mathcal{K}}=\hbar v_{F}\vec{\sigma}\cdot\vec{p}.
\]

\end_inset

Confinement to enclosure: use a mass term outside to open a gap in energies
 close to zero 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{H}_{\mathcal{K}}=\hbar v_{F}\vec{\sigma}\cdot\vec{p}+m\left(\vec{r}\right)\left(\sigma_{z}-\cos\theta\right).
\]

\end_inset

The necessary condition is imposing zero normal probability current 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{j}_{\mathrm{normal}}=v_{F}\Psi^{\dagger}\vec{\sigma}_{\mathrm{normal}}\Psi=0.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hard boundary: let 
\begin_inset Formula $m\left(\vec{r}\right)\to\infty$
\end_inset

 outside the enclosure 
\begin_inset Formula $\Longrightarrow$
\end_inset

 BC for an edge at an angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 with the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

-axis
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\psi_{B}}{\psi_{A}}=te^{i\alpha},\,\,\,t\in\mathit{Reals}.
\]

