\begin_layout Subsection
Infinite-Mass Confined Square
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To apply this method to 
\begin_inset Formula $t=1$
\end_inset

 square, the initial spinor is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Psi_{0}\left(x,y\right)=N_{0}\left[\left[\frac{L^{2}}{4}-x^{2}\right]\left(\begin{array}{c}
1\\
-\frac{2y}{L}
\end{array}\right)+\left[\frac{L^{2}}{4}-y^{2}\right]\left(\begin{array}{c}
1\\
\frac{2ix}{L}
\end{array}\right)\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Applying again the G-S process, we square the Dirac Hamiltonian to eliminate
 the valence band,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\bra{\Psi_{i}}H^{\dagger}H\ket{\Psi_{j}} & =-\hbar^{2}v_{F}^{2}\bra{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\psi_{i,A}\\
\psi_{i,B}
\end{array}\right)}\left(\begin{array}{cc}
\nabla^{2} & 0\\
0 & \nabla^{2}
\end{array}\right)\ket{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\psi_{j,A}\\
\psi_{j,B}
\end{array}\right)}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

